<br>
Thought of another book if anyone is interested...<br>
<br>
True sattire, not comedy - and it's a sci-fi fantasy:  Mission Earth (by L.Ron.Hubbard) <br>
<br>
It's an aboslute riot to read...  Each book is 500-800 pages long, and there are 10 books in the story.  I think it ended up winning a TON of rewards and is still considered the the biggest 'story' ever written...  You can read the first couple of pages from the Translator (the book is a 'transcription of a report about a planet called Earth that can't possibly exist') just to get an idea of what the book is like....<br>
<br>
Definitely one of my favorite sets of books....<br>
<br>
*rerails the thread....*<br>
