<br>
Anyhow, one of the questions he asked was how he was planning on finishing his series without dragging the story on like Robert Jordan.  Martin actually told him that was a major concern of his and that he didn't want that to happen.<br>
<br>
Apparently, Martin sympathized with Jordan saying something about publishers, deadlines and not being able to plan out a storyline any further out than one book at a time.<br>
<br>
Anyway back on topic.  I liked the Wheel of Time series up until book six then I was lost.  As far as fantasy goes, Martin's my new favorite with Fiest coming in second (very much like Jordan only in smaller doses).<br>
