I liked the Mallorean and the Tamuli. Both expanded their respective worlds a great deal and allowed for more character development. A particular favorite of mine was Zakath.<br>
<br>
That said, David Eddings' best series is the Elenium.It has a grim, dark foreboding feeling to it, is well written, and has a fascinating cast of characters.Tamuli is second place. THEN Mallorean and Belgariad tie for third.<br>
<br>
Back to WoT.<br>
<br>
Yeesh. Drag yer heels, people, won't you? I used to like WoT, but in the last book I read, Crossroads of Twilight....NOTHING HAPPENED. The WoT has never been my favorite anyways. It's all right....but hardly as good as it gets credit for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mercfv>Merc FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/22/04 10:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2347.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grrrrr Robert Jordan Series</span><hr size=1> More derailing....<br>
<br>
I'm totally on the G.R.R.M bandwagon.  Wonderful characters.  Quality writing with enough unexpected twists and turns to keep you reading.   How often these days can you say you are really surprised by the plot twists you read in most SF/fantasy work?<br>
<br>
Another author/series to add to the mix:  the series that begins with Kushiel's Dart and continues with Kushiel's Chosen and Kushiel's Avatar.  Can't remember the author's name -- Jaqueline Carey seems to stick in my mind, but I'm not sure.  Superb writing with a very textured feel to it.  Highly recommend it if you like some of the other books mentioned. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=2347.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=2347.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=2347.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2347.topic&index=32><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.threadControl?topicID=2347.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2347.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2347.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email noti